$ .git/description

By default, `→ development/version-control-systems/git/_git[.git]/description` contains the text `Unnamed reposotitory; edit this file 'description' to name the repository`.

It seems that this file can be used in → development/version-control-systems/git/_git/hooks[hook scripts] or by
*GitWeb* to display the repo's description on the *GitWeb page*.
